entry.title: Dictation: Fix disabled tests
entry.content:
The on-device variant of DictationTest were disabled due to high levels

of flakes. The reason for failure is in the

SendFinalResultAndWaitForEditableValue method; after sending a speech

result, we wait for a value changed event to be fired. For network

variants of this test, this works and is stable, but for on-device

variants, this never gets satisfied. The most plausible explanation

here is that on-device speech results get returned more slowly, and

by the time we call WaitForValueChangedEvent, the value changed event

has already been dispatched.



The fix here is to wait for a value changed event only if we're using

network speech recognition.



Fixed: 1490612

entry.title: Report browser process list in TabManagerDelegate
entry.content:
The tab process list is sent to the resource manager daemon (resourced).

The tab process list is used to estimate the memory usage of the

background and protected processes. Based on the Chrome memory usage,

resourced determines when to release memory from Chrome or VMs or

container. When there are a lot of background processes in Ash Chrome,

resourced avoids killing perceptible apps in VMs or container.



The process list reporting feature is already implemented in

OomScorePolicyChromeOS in performance_manager. Also implement the

process list reporting in TabManagerDelegate so the resonsive balloon

feature doesn't have to depend on feature

AshUrgentDiscardingFromPerformanceManager.

entry.title: Define an extensions.mojom.ServiceWorker interface
entry.content:
This is a reland of 14dccee82412b81286653d579b50dc565c85ca31 but

with support for conditional compilation.



Push the permissions from the browser to each service worker so

that we avoid racing with the main thread when permissions

are updated.



Currently if a permission update is sent it is sent via the

extensions.mojom.Renderer interface and all these events are propagated

to the WorkerThreads. In order to unblock the ResponseWorkerAck message

from not hitting the main thread and directly going to the worker

thread (as a callback on extensions.ServiceWorkerHost.RequestWorker)

we proactively push the updated permissions on the associated channel

with the ServiceWorker. This avoids the race that will happen.



This is tested by ExtensionApiTest.EventAfterPermissionRemoved

entry.title: [AWC] Implement `window.setResizable(bool)` JS API
entry.content:
This CL does the following:

- Adds a new variable `window_resizable_from_web_api_` to track the

web API -manipulated resizability of a widget so that it's possible to

separate the non-tampered resizability value if e.g. navigating /

switching tabs.

- Makes `BrowserView` observe

`WidgetObserver:OnWidgetSizeConstraintsChanged` which enables observing

any change to the size constraints of the widget (including changes to

`can_resize_` or `window_resizable_from_web_api_` which can be updated

with the new `window.setResizable(bool)` API).

- Updates the `resizable` CSS media@ feature when the observer is

called.

- Ensures navigating resets `can_resize_from_web_api` value. This should

in most of the cases be limited by the lack of `window-management`

permission already, but it could be possible that one would navigate

into another URL, which also has the permission granted already.

entry.title: [iOS] Fix Safety Check (Magic Stack) module layout for Dynamic Type.
entry.content:
This change introduces two fixes for how the Safety Check (Magic Stack)

module handles Dynamic Type, especially at larger font sizes:



1. The "Last run time..." subtitle in the Magic Stack module container

will now properly grow/shrink depending on Dynamic Type; it's also now

properly aligned for RTL and LTR languages.

properly take up their respective space at larger font sizes; the title

is prioritized, while the description is de-prioritized.
